# Jinja2 模板与静态资源规范

> 来源：[PatrickJS/awesome-cursorrules](https://github.com/PatrickJS/awesome-cursorrules) shopify-theme-dev-liquid · 已映射到 FastAPI + Jinja2 结构

## Project Structure

- **Templates**: `app/templates/*.html` — one page per route; shared layout in `base.html`.
- **Macros**: reusable fragments in `_macros.html` (`page_header`, `render_plan_tree`, etc.).
- **Static**: `app/templates/static/style.css` + `app.js` — no separate webpack/vite unless requested.
- **Pages router**: `app/routers/pages.py` passes context; do not hardcode user-specific data in templates.

## Jinja2 Templating

- Use `{% extends "base.html" %}` and `{% block content %}` consistently.
- Extract repeated UI into `{% macro %}` in `_macros.html`.
- Keep complex logic in Python (services/pages.py); templates only display and light conditionals.
- Use `{% for %}...{% else %}` for empty states, not blank tables.
- Prefer `|tojson` filter when passing data to `<script>` blocks (Chart.js, etc.).

## JavaScript in Templates

- Page-specific scripts go in `{% block scripts %}` at bottom of template.
- Shared helpers (`showToast`, `parseError`) live in `app.js`.
- Use event listeners in script blocks, not inline handlers for new features.

## CSS Styling

- Use CSS variables defined in `:root` inside `style.css`.
- Component classes: `.card-app`, `.panel-form`, `.table-app`, `.ring-card`, `.plan-tree`.
- Responsive: Bootstrap breakpoints + `@media` for custom components.
- Do not duplicate Bootstrap utilities in custom CSS unless overriding brand.

## Performance

- Minimize inline styles; prefer classes.
- Chart.js loaded via CDN only on pages that need charts.
- Avoid N+1 in templates — aggregate data in services before render.

## Accessibility (A11y)

- All interactive elements keyboard accessible.
- Meaningful `alt` on images; `aria-label` on icon-only buttons.
- Semantic HTML before ARIA.
- Color contrast WCAG AA; status not color-only (use badges/text).
- Visible focus states; respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.

## Maintenance

- Match existing naming and indentation in templates.
- Do not break `fetch()` API paths or form field `name` attributes.
- Test both logged-in and empty-data states when changing list/table templates.
